Find the year anchor. Starting with year 1826:
 - first take the century digits C = Y / 100 = 1826 / 100 = 18
 - and remainder dividing by four C = C % 4 = 18 % 4 = 2
 - then take the last two digits D = Y % 100 = 1826 % 100 = 26
 - and remainder dividing by four E = D % 4 = 26 % 4 = 2
 - add together to get W = 5*((C + E) - 1) + 10*D = 5*((2 + 2) - 1) + 10*26 = 275 ≡ Tuesday
